        <ontology:partOfNarrative rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/narrative/N147_VC_08_SER"/>
        <ontology:took_place_at rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/phenomenal_place/43.648333333_19.679166666"/>
        <ontology:took_place_at rdf:resource="https://dlnarratives.eu/place/0"/>
        <ontology:hasDescription>The reference mountain chain of this VC is Western Serbia, Dinaric Alps region. The reference mountain landscape of this VC is Zlatibor mountain. Zlatibor mountain is rich in natural, cultural and historical assets. Its climate and high number of sunny hours per year ismaking this area suitable for health tourism (air spa), as well as other types of tourism. Main economic activities, besides tourism are agriculture, processing industry (meat, dairy etc.) and wood processing.The area is rich in waters, with two artifical lakes, used for water supply. Flora and fauna are also very rich, with many medical herbs and wild animals like wolfs. The area is very popular for living, and there is very small reduction in population numbers.  </ontology:hasDescription>
    </NamedIndividual>
    


